S University is really hard , for me both of these solutions have adantages and inconveniences . Living with your family have many advantages ; You are helped by them and you do not have to pay the rent , the food . They are an emotional support for you . But , there are a lot of inconveniences ; for example , you do not have your intimity , you ca not leave and returns to the house when you want , you ca not invite friends . But the worst is that they can perturbate your revisions , you can be devloved . Remind it : too much emotion equal to less stability . Living alone have more advantages ; You have all your intimity , you can make choices that you want , for example you can eat when you want . You do not have to do the housework everyday because you have your organization . And finally , you have all the calm for study because no one can disturb you . But there are inconvenient too ; you can feel alone sometimes , and your food is not as good as your parents , moreover you do not have a lot of money , then you do not eat so much . You have to resolve your own problems ... I prefer live alone because it develop autonomy and organization .
