S I am a teacher and I had this experience in my studies as a student and my career as a teacher First : as a student you have must know and learn of the different methods to studying and build learn skills from more than one teacher where every teacher have a special way of teaching then that experience make your learning more flexible and able to more learning whatever the difficulties . Second : even with a weak teacher you will be able to self -learning specifically within the Internet which is brought up a major revolution in the self -learning field and I always say to my students they can replace any teacher in their school with the Internet where there is a countless website to learn any material you want whether on Youtube or any learning platform in various fields . Learning from only one teacher makes the student passive in his learning and limits his ability to learn from a variety of sources Finally : Perhaps in primary school the children 's students need one teacher in order to the strong establish in learning reading and writing basics .
