S I think that studying abroad can give you lots of great experiences and could also make you more independent . But I think that the most advantage is the opportunity of knowing yourself far away from the look of your parents , family and friends . It gives you the freedom of discovering sides of you that you did not know of . Some of them you will enjoy and some of them you wo not , but you can work on those that you did not like and make a better version of yourself . But there will be also the feeling of loneliness , especially in the first months . The knowdledge among with it adventure is also a huge experience . The school ´s structure and the educational system will be different from what you were used to and you will have to adjuste yourself in this whole new world . The school ´s colleagues will be probably from different countries . So , the challenge of living together with people from different countries gives the opportunity of facing different opinions , cultures and habits . This will give personal and professional growth . There is also the big opportunity of being fluent in a new language . This will improve your resumé and you will be a footstep ahead on the journey of finding a job .
