S If I had to do a retrospective of my educational growth , I would say that I ´m at a higher level on the following areas : mathematics , physics and chemistry . This is definitely because those are the subjects that I ´m pleased with and because of it I spend more time studying them . I think it ´s because I like to read the theory and then exercise what I ´ve learned . Furthermore , I enjoy the objectivity that it comes with those subjects . So , for this year I just intend to keep following the same schedule and commitment that I did last year with those subjects . On the other hand , I did not spend enough time on studying the subjects that I do not like as geography , history and biology . In this year , I have to try harder and spend at least 20 minutes per day for each subject . When I start studying them , I get really grumpy and this makes me give up . So , I intend to start the daily routine with a subject that I like , so that my mood and energy could increase enough for studying those which I do not like . I hope that this will end up being a good strategy .
