S Giove , a little village in Umbria , the green heart of Italy . Giove is about 100 kilometers from Rome and there is a train station . This village is very famous , thanks to his big medieval castle . The castle has 365 windows , one for each day of the years . In Giove , you can eat in several typical restaurants but , there is not souvenir shops or other types of shops . Sometimes , the citizens organised village festivals for tourists . It is a beautiful location . Let 's go !
