S Lots people think that good school results are only granted if teachers do not change over the years ; some others believe that a change amid the teachers over the years can be more beneficial . I would start by setting a time range as students have needs differentiated by age : pupils in the primary school certainly need to have a referred point , one teacher to apply not only for school subjects but also as a guide their psychological growth . In the secondary school , instead , in my opinion , students need a change , they need to experience different referees : they will have to begin and face the alternative nuances that life could offer and what a good opportunity by starting at school , with a teacher for various subjects ! At College , students are gown up already and they can start to enrich their culture . This is the stage where they have already started to broaden their life vision by embrancing the alternative view points , more professors can be a wide source in this direction . I strongly believe that the richness of human beings is in the variety , in any respect ! BH
