S Music at school ? Music as a school subject or how to learn and play an instrument is compulsory in a few schools while in some others , students are not required to do so . I think that music should always be added as subject to learn in each school at any level being far important to the emotional growth of scholars and as alternative way of learning about history . Just to give an example , learning about the history of music may give the students the opportunity to know about a part of human evolution . If you name , for instance , the period of romanticism , studying Wagner could make them understand the vision of the intellectuals in the nineteenth century . In addition , learning how to play an instrument can definitely help the development of a manual intellegence as well as a sensitive one in most of the students . Although listening to music can be relaxing , learning how to play it might become a more effective tool to use when you need to get rid of the stress . In my view , I wish to underline again the importance of studying music as a school subject at any degree as it will enrich the students ' inner world then it will broaden their emotional horizon and in the end , it will add another way to communicate : Music is absolutely another language which can easily talk to heart and soul .
