S Dear sir , I read an article in a newspaper said that the town council is planning to ban using mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . In my opinion , I think it is not a good idea because of some reasons bellow : First , today mobile phones are the smart phones . People use smart phones for many purposes such as working , sudying , communicating , etc . Many people do not finish their works before going home and they have to work on the way home . They have to use mobile phones to continue their work . I have applied for this job for 6 months and I have to study more to increase my knowledge and I often use my mobile phone to study the online course on the way going home . I have to save every minute . If the town councile bans using mobile phones on public transport , how could I study any more . I knew that many young people use their mobile phones to study their additional courses in free time . Second , online payment is developing very fast , many people use mobile phones to pay their bills when shopping . I knew that our government encouraged people to use electronic payment . it helps the economic system more transparent . If the town council bans using mobile phones in shops , people have to use cash for their payment and the policy of using online payment of government cannot be conducted . I am a responsible person and I find my responsibility for our country . I would like to recommend that the town council should not isue that ban .
