S Studying at university is an important choice in life and as a consequence , in relation to the chosen school , it is sometimes necessary to move from home . Some students decide then to leave home and stay on their own while some others choose to stay by their families . The first decisive factor , establishing whether to stay with parents while studying at the univesity or to leave home , is the economic aspect which most of the times determines as well the choice of the univerisity to attend . In my opinion , I would suggest staying home with parents so that students could totally dedicate their time to study instead of trying to balance school and job . Thinking just about the school may help to get over the university in due time and obvisouly by respecting the timetable , it results in an additional cost saving . On the other hand , if students decide to leave home and live by themeselves while studying , they have first of all to consider the additional cost of a rented apartment . They need then to start thinking of their life as an adult one with all its consequeces . For example , they definitely need to look after their new house , think on how to arrange the daily routine such as shopping for meals or cleaning the house . All actions that take time from their studies . In addition , should they need to look for a job to gain a living , they will have lesser time for school . In some cases , this situation can lead the students to withdraw from university . At the end , I strongly believe that the best and the most effective way to study at the University is to choose a school not very far from parents ' home in order to stay with parents and dedicate all the energy towards the successful conclusion of the school career .
