S An environment that provides comfort and silence it is almost always the perfect place for any worker at a work place . When you give privacy to an employee , he feels comfortable , calm , relaxed and safe . Those characteristics remind him of a safe place and because of that , he will be more open and free to be himself out of the looks , pressure and critical expressions and words of his co -workers . This private area will relax him enough to induce his criativity and productivity . The results of an enclosed workstation will appear at the quality of the work presented by the employees and also at the amount and agility of the tasks done by them daily . On the other hand , those offices with open design do not have walls that can provide privacy to the employees . The privacy that comes with the walls offers a distance from the pressure caused by critical looks from co -workers and also offers a certain sound barrier between them . The lack of sound barrier is probably one of the main reasons why workers get so distracted during their daily work . When you are at an environment that you do not feel comfortable enough to do your job , it can be quite challenging to achieve your level of concentration to start a task . When you finally got back on track , someone starts talking on the phone or with someone near you . That action disturbs anyone , even the most focused person and you will get a hard time trying to keep going with your work . Even though when those conversations are over , you will spend another few minutes to get back to the rhythm and the level of concentration that you were before you were interrupted . Those precious minutes stolen from you daily due to the loss of focus , will certainly affect not just your productivity and quality , but also the entire office .
