S Dear town council , I wrote this letter because 15 families from Star Street had chosen me to be delegate , this letter articulate all Star Streets villigers emotions , feelings and thoughts . I have been living in this town for 70 years . I was born in this town . Me and my family 's daily routines were very diffiucult when I was a child . There were no technological devices , machines for farming and communicating devices but that was 65 years ago . I and many of town members wished to have some technology . There were different members in town councils in those years . One day they asked us if we wanted to have telephones . Then they said they would get the substructure ready for telephone lines . On that day we got used to use mobile phones everywhere . We all have been very thankful to old town council because mobile phone made very big change in our lives . We all had been using our mobile phones happily before this bad idea was clarified by town council . Many of us have children , relatives and grandchildren who live in city centers ; we want to communicate with them easily everywhere . We like our town 's development . We all agree that we have a right to make phone calls , send messages to put it simple use mobile phone . We do not want you to introduce that kind of law in our town . Best regards , Eva Sparks and The Star Street Villigers .
