S Nowadays , the internet and The way of life at home contribute to the inactive lifestyle , the citizens can without step out the door but get the takeaway and all of the things that life necessity , so somebody come up with a idel that all university students and school children should be forced to do sports at least 3 times per week . As far as I 'm concerned , I ca not agree with this idea , it is good to promote national exercise , but should not be forced but should be channelled . First and foremost , people of all ages have something they must do , like the students , they have to prepare for the term final exam , and the fresh man need to study hard to get credits , and the graduates may have prepared for interview and work hard until steady so that they ca not do sprots , so , it will intensify many society contradictions , moreover , it may causing trouble for a lot of people . Additionally , there are variety of approaches to deal with national inactive lifestyle phenomenon but not the only way to force students and children work out at least 3 times every week , for example , the government can hold some citizens games , or shot some promote video to encourage the individuals work out frequently which can benefit them a lot , all this way are better than force them to do sports . What 's more , teenagers and children may have the reble mentality , and I convinced that if the government wanna to implement some policies , some punitive measures are bound to be enacted , in that case , some family do not want their children be punished , so they will force them to do sports which teenagers and children do not want to do , so the gaps of renlationship will appeare which will lead to truancy rate surge , and finally cuase the suicide rate increase . All in all , I know it is critical to improve national physical fitness , and let the young love the feel of going outside but not sit in morden buliding all the day , but may some better options could be chosen .
