S For some people it may not be a compete rocket science however some may wrap their head around this question I 'm about to present . Would you rather live a long calm life or would you prefer short but intense life instead ? Let 's dive into that ... On one hand we have long peaceful life , which I bet many introverts would according to studies choose over chaotic intense life . Life full of happiness , friends or even family . Sounds like a dream come true , does not it ? Have you ever wondered though what you 'd do with this long period of time in your hands ? Your life might get bored after a while not doing anything exciting . On the other hand however we have short yet more intense life full of adventure , memories and good laughs . This option sounds more appalling to outgoing and sociable people . There are cons to this option for certain and it 's up to every single one what seems more likeable to them . I , personally , would without a doubt choose the second option being shorter yet more intense life . I 'm aware nobody specified the exact period of time I 'd get to live , nonetheless picturing myself siting on sofa maybe rading a book for perhaps 60 years seems like a waste of my time whereas adventures even small ones for instant simply appeal more exciting and I desire a life where I can turn back to see what I happened to achieve or simply look back with a smile on my face knowing I have done everything I 'd wished for .
