S Some people believe that it is good for students to have the same teacher for several years . Others think that students benefit more from new teachers each year . I think both options are good , when the students have the same teacher for several years , they will understand the model of the teaching that the teacher has and will adapt themselves to focus more os classes than on things like the uncertainty about which teacher they will have in the next class . Nonetheless , have different teachers is good too , when the students have new teachers every year , they might be more sociable compared to other students , they adapt themselves to other realities , have other opinions and ppints of views , and are more adapted to real live situations when they will meet new people every day . How I argue , the fist or the second option have benefits and issues , the better option is to choose a hibrid model , mixing both options to improve the students knowledge and adapt them to different situations . We can only choose a teacher for the student 's first five years and after making them choose a different teacher each year , in this model we can have the benefit of both options and reduce the bias we could have adopted only one option . If we analyse our learning model , we can see a lack of opportunities of learning that restricts the skill of students just because we do not think about our learning models , we need try something different to have different results . Think about the possibilities we have today if we use the digital tools that are available , we have the chance to create a model that really changes the way we learn things . Think about it .
