S When we are undergraduates , we are just at the beginning of our life , we do not know many things and we are experiencing new realities , feelings and living new moments that build our personality over time . Some students move and live alone wile others choose to live at home with their family , let 's talk about these two options . Both options have vantagens and disadvantages , the first option improve more experiences to students than the second one , when students decide to live in a campus or rent an apartment close to the university , they will learn how the adult live is , they will understand a reality that was different that they have in their parents ' house , they will learn things that only the life impose to them . Live alone is a challenge for everyone , but is a great moment when they can grow faster . The second option is more comfortable , when a student keep living at parents ' house during college time , they will save more money compared to move away to live in their own . In contrast , many opportunities and experiences will be lost comparatively . Another advantage of living with parents is the fact that they have more free time to focus on the subjects they need learn . Both options are good , sometimes a student does not have the option to choose , a student must live with his parents because he has not enough money to live by herself for example , sometimes , the parents ' house is very far from the university that student must move away to live closer and spent less time and money . Despite the options , the most important thing for students is not this short time they will live with parents or not , what matters is learn new things and be happy with what they have at the moment .
