S Telling the truth has been always considered to many people that are very good people and they in all occasions tell the truth about everything , but ... . Is always telling the truth the best option ? Telling the truth is one of the best options , but not in everything , if you gotta tell that for example , a dog of a person has died and he/she is asking you and you know what happened , you can tell him/her that his/her dog has disappeared to do not make them very sad about their dog has died , but not always telling a lie to try to " fix " something could fix that , it could end up in a very very bad situation , as an example , you can tell that you did not break up that jar , but if your mother believes it , she then will go to ask your brother/sister , then to your father and then they will ask you to tell what you saw , and if you lied the punishment of breaking a jar will be bigger as you lied to them too . What you can do to prevent those scenarios you could take like 10 seconds to analyse the question they did to you to think about " shall I tell the truth ? Or a little lie ? " then you can say the best option , but in the scenario you could not think about it you can just say " I do not know "
