S Hello , I heard about a plan to ban mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants , who has this idea ? I ask because there is no possibility what people will not use their mobile phones in these places . What was the person proposing this thinking ? Today we use our smartphone to do many things , some people pay for public transport with an app , use virtual reality to try on clothes and use their cameras to access restaurant menus through QR codes displayed on the tables . there are no laws that will restrict the use of smartphones anywhere , there is only one place where people do not use their smartphones , I 'm talking about high secure areas where these devices are restricted by law . If the intent of this plan is to reduce mobile phones use to improve people 's quality of life , banning it is not the right answer . We need teach people about the health problems that using their smarphones for loung hours cause on their health , we can establish rules of social behavior for some places , not to force people do what we want , but to achieve our goals by doing with people choosing themselves correct behavior in those places . We just have to make suggestions to create the right culture , people 's habits will change naturally to suit the local culture . This is the right way to influence them to do what we want .
