S Hello there , As in this magazine is looking for some reviews , I 'm lending to you reader , my review about Write And Improve . The way I found it , I was looking for some ways to improve my English , why ? Because the English is the most spoken language and I wanted to do something with it . Now , the interesting part about the review . The first step is a common step , just sign in or log in , after it , you could see at the up left corner , " Welcome ( your name ) and a sign out button in blue , as it says , it 's to sign out from your account , down it you " ll see " W&I woorkbooks " just click there to open every type of workbook that W&I has . There is the IELTS Academic test , IELTS General Training and B2 First . Below it you 'll see " My workbooks ' . " My workbooks " It is for creating a new workbook or joining a one , down it you 'll see " Create a workbook " and as its name says . It 's for creating a workbook , down it you 'll see " Join a workbook , and that is just to join a workbook , even there is more than you thought , there 's still more things to see . Below the option : " join a workbook " there is the option " Class View " . For now that 's for teachers , that helps teachers to see what their students have done , after you 'll see Progress , My account and Help centre . Progress is to see your achievements of W&I , my account is for looking at your profile with more detail , and help centre is for asking for some help , or reporting any errors . Why did I wrote all that text if you could practice that ? Easy , because this is a review of my experience and I wanted to say to English learners that just found W&I . Anyways . Taking my experience with W&I , I could just say that , there are not many errors as in other websites . The important things are very easy placed and very comfortable to you to founding them . Good day . Directly , from unknown English learner .
